    "narrative": "The clear priority for today\u2019s lineup is **Lawrence Butler**, who commands the day's highest score at 74.61. A favorable matchup against Fedde (5.60 xERA) combined with a 10% park factor boost and a significant platoon advantage makes him an essential start. Similarly, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (70.83) serves as our offensive anchor; while the platoon edge against Kremer is neutral, his raw base projection remains peerless, and he is locked into the three-hole. For managers tracking our scarcest category, **Masyn Winn** (62.13) offers high-leverage upside; his matchup against McCullers Jr. is favorable, and his sprint speed profile remains the primary driver behind his strong utilization today.\n\nWe are navigating a cluster of marginal starts, with **Cal Raleigh** (44.43) representing our most difficult decision. Despite his power upside, he faces a tough assignment against Eovaldi (3.17 xERA) and faces a negative park adjustment, keeping his score well below our strong-start threshold. On the bench, **Wenceel Perez** (48.60) was the closest to cracking the lineup. While he benefits from a positive park factor against Bello, his score was suppressed by a \"wind-in\" risk and a suboptimal spot in the batting order, ultimately leading us to favor the higher-floor volume of **Jung Hoo Lee** (58.45). We are also monitoring the defensive risks posed by the elite catcher arms facing **Matt Chapman**, **Drew Gilbert**, and **Jung Hoo Lee**, which marginally tempers their stolen base outlooks despite favorable matchups against Cavalli.",
